The Telegraph - Calcutta
		 Thursday, January 16, 2003 				 Its India vs Bangla in semis
																								SAFF CUP																								Dhaka: Holders India come up against Bangladesh in the second semi-final of the South Asian Football Federation (SAFF) Cup on Saturday.																								In Group B matches on Wednesday Bangladesh thrashed Bhutan 3-0 to confirm their top position in the group, while the Maldives pipped Nepal 3-2 to finish runners-up. 																								Pakistan, group A toppers, meet the Maldives in the other semi-finals. Bangladesh scored through Ariful Kabir in the third and 51st minutes. Rokonuzzaman Kanchan rounded off the tally in the 78th minute.																								Nepal and Bhutan drop out of the meet from group B. The final will be held on Monday. (REUTERS)
